translated: Dahlström, Karl Warner, construction manager, Lidköping, born on March 5th, 1903 in Gävle to district manager Karl Fredrik D. and Johanna Larsson. Married in 1933 to Edit Sundberg. Children: Hans born in 1934, Birgit born in 1939. He took the final exam of his studies in Gävle in 1922 and received his degree from KTH (VoV) in 1927. He worked as assistant engineer at Gävle City Power Plant and Tramways from 1927 to 1931, as bureau engineer at Gävle Building Office from 1931 to 1934, as works engineer at Örebro Building Office from 1934 to 1938, and as construction manager in Lidköping since 1938. He was a board member of the Swedish Gas Works Association since 1946, and a member of the Swedish Engineering Association and Swedish Road and Water Building National Association. He was a member of Odd Fellow and a board member of Rotary. He was also a member of the Swedish Air Force Association with the rank of Lieutenant Colonel.
